               <head>Abvab al-jinan of Qazvini</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Abvāb al-jinān by Vāʿiẓ Qazvīnī, Muḥammad Rafīʿ</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85045106 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91005357 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111616" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3752-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Ethical compendium based on the Qurʾān and the moral precepts of the Twelve Imams, planned in eight abvāb with only a portion surviving, dedicated to the Safavid ruler, Shāh ʿAbbās II (d. 1077/1667)
</p>
                        <p>Replacement folios (relatively early) added ff. 2-7; crude replacement on f. 1v, which is the inside of the front flap
</p>
                        <p>Fungal damage and water stains
</p>
                        <p>Original folios often marked at top as vaqf al-ʿāmm; good nastaʿlīq and naskh; gold ruled jadāval throughout
</p>
                        <p>Annotated in margins; some owner seals: 1) Muṣṭafá; 2) Yār ʿAlī ibn Salīm
</p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 17 Jul. 1908
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
